# Delta Learn Backend

Django 6 + DRF + SQLite. Single app `chapters` for all content models, `users` for auth.

## Architecture

```
Delta-Learn-Backend/
├── delta_learn/          # Settings, root urls, wsgi
├── chapters/             # All content models, views, serializers, admin, management commands
├── users/                # Register, login (JWT), /me
└── fixtures/             # JSON seed data
```

## API Endpoints (all under `/api/`)

### Public
- `GET subjects/` — list with chapter_count, written_count
- `GET subjects/{slug}/` — detail + chapter index
- `GET subjects/{slug}/chapters/{number}/` — full chapter with questions + takeaways

### Auth (`auth/`)
- `POST auth/register/` — create account
- `POST auth/login/` — JWT access + refresh tokens
- `POST auth/token/refresh/` — refresh access token
- `GET auth/me/` — current user (Bearer)

### Admin CRUD (`manage/` — IsAdminUser)
- CRUD: `manage/subjects/`, `manage/chapters/`, `manage/questions/`, `manage/takeaways/`
- `POST manage/chapters/{id}/stage-populate/` — bulk replace via staged request (IsAuthenticated)

### Staged Requests (`staged/` — IsAuthenticated)
- `POST staged/` — create staged request
- `GET staged/` — list (own for users, all for admin; `?status=`, `?target_model=` filters)
- `POST staged/{id}/approve/` — admin applies change
- `POST staged/{id}/reject/` — admin rejects with note

### User-scoped (IsAuthenticated)
- `highlights/` — list/create, `highlights/{id}/` — patch/delete
- `notes/` — list/create, `notes/{id}/` — CRUD, `notes/{id}/analyze/` — AI placeholder

### DeltaMails (AllowAny for subscribe/unsubscribe)
- `deltamails/` — list, `deltamails/subscribe/` — create
- `deltamails/{id}/preferences/` — patch (IsAuthenticated)
- `deltamails/unsubscribe/` — deactivate by email + subject

### Docs
- `schema/` — OpenAPI YAML, `docs/` — Swagger, `redoc/` — ReDoc

## Staged Request System

- `target_model`: subject | chapter | question | takeaway | **chapter_populate**
- `chapter_populate`: payload has `{chapter_title, questions: [...], takeaways: [...]}`
- On approval: `apply()` executes the operation; `chapter_populate` deletes old + creates new atomically
- Admin panel: rich styled HTML preview, default pending filter, bulk approve/reject actions

## Management Commands

| Command | Purpose | Schedule |
|---------|---------|----------|
| `seed_data` | Load fixtures into DB | One-time |
| `seed_topics` | Populate EmailTopic from chapters | One-time |
| `refresh_topics` | AI discovers new topics via Gemma | Weekly cron |
| `send_deltamails` | Send emails to active subscribers | Daily cron |

## Models (chapters app)

| Model | Key Fields |
|-------|-----------|
| Subject | slug (unique), name, description, accent_color, order |
| Chapter | subject FK, chapter_number, part, title, subtitle, order |
| Question | chapter FK, order, question, difficulty, tldr, answer, points (JSON), diagram, diagram2, table_data (JSON), followup |
| Takeaway | chapter FK, order, content (HTML) |
| Highlight | user FK, chapter FK, question_index, text, color |
| Note | user FK, subject FK?, chapter FK?, content, ai_summary |
| StagedRequest | operation, target_model, target_id?, payload (JSON), status, requested_by FK, reviewed_by FK |
| Subscription | email, subject FK, user FK?, difficulty, custom_prompt, is_active |
| EmailTopic | subject FK, title, keywords (JSON), source, chapter FK? |
| SentHistory | subscription FK, topic FK, sent_at, questions_json (JSON) |

## Conventions

- JWT via simplejwt (access 1h, refresh 14d)
- Serializer naming: camelCase for reads (frontend), snake_case for writes
- CORS: localhost:5173, delta-learn.netlify.app (env-configurable)
- Env vars: `DJANGO_SECRET_KEY`, `DJANGO_DEBUG`, `ALLOWED_HOSTS`, `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`, `DB_PATH`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD`

### Adding a new model
1. Define in `chapters/models.py` with `Meta.ordering` and `__str__`
2. Register in `chapters/admin.py` with list_display, list_filter
3. Create serializer in `chapters/serializers.py`
4. Add view in `chapters/views.py` with `@extend_schema` tags
5. Add route in `chapters/urls.py`
6. Run `makemigrations && migrate`
